Be Present🙏👊
.
If you’ve been following me for a while you know I post my fitness on here and I’m very opened with what’s going on in my life and how I’m feeling. I kinda treat my IG like a journal sometimes. Ive had this audio saved for several months now but hadn’t used it because it wasn’t the right time, I wasn’t at peace. To say I’m at peace right now is a pretty big deal to me. I no longer sweat the little things, the things that don’t even exist and you’re just making a whole movie in your head. Guys The future doesn’t exist, stop being anxious about things that aren’t even here yet. Be present, focus on what you have infront of you. The last 2 years have been very hard for me (iykyk) but now… things have faded. What changed? Well, I decided to change my environment and the people around me. Crazy to say it but things seem to be so much better. The way I feel internally is fkn solid, I feel at peace. I feel happy. Im not worried about shit. Im welcoming my 30s with the best mindset and heart ever. #thankyousnowboarding #thankyoukettebells

SNATCH TECHNIQUE🔥💪🏽
.
Happy Sunday Fam!! We are going over the snatch technique with a virtual client so I figured to share it on here as well and bring some value to you guys!
.
When you’re doing the snatch, think about having that KB as close as possible to the body the entire time. When you are in the transition from the hike position to the overhead position, think about letting the KB float while you slightly pull the KB towards you by bending at the elbow (to avoid overcasting) and the moment you are at about forehead level, think about extending the arm to the ceiling, or punching Up so you can have a smooth landing on the forearm/wrist.
.
For the way down, same but different. You will start by bending / flicking the wrist and then the elbow and think about driving your elbow towards your ribs to avoid overcasting the KB. Once that KB is about Belly button height, absorb that force by hinging properly and engaging the core as hard as you can so you don’t start feeling it in the lower back later on.
.
Ps: heavy snatches will def give you some posterior chain gains!😉💪🏽

POWER CHAIN🔥💪🏽
.
Want to get stronger on one leg? Give this staggered stance KB chain a try. Something I always like to think about when I’m hitting staggered stance exercises is to make it seem like I were to be standing on one leg. This is a solid way to introduce single leg training to your program. Especially for those of you that are always doing machine stuff or your typical bilateral stance exercises. Mix it up every now and then. It’s only going to benefit you in the long run. So many different ways you can train on one leg but today I chose staggered stance for this power chain.
.
Tip: Notice how everything stays in line, notice how I keep the KB as close as possible to the body on that clean and snatch. All the force is coming from the ground Up! Think about like you’re trying to jump on one leg and make sure to lock in as you get to the top of each movement.
.
Who’s this for? For any athletes who’s playing ball, running, mixed martial arts, snowboarders & skiers. And if you aren’t, you should still put in this work and continue bettering yourself.
